fix(build,ui,config): APK-bundled native backends, portrait scanner, bare base64 bundles

Four user-visible blockers addressed in one push so the next CI build
produces an installable APK with all three protocols actually bundled:

1. About still shows "not bundled (noop mode)" (root cause of #4 too).
   The umbrella paykeyfearnative.aar was pulled in via `fileTree(*.aar)`
   on the :app module. AGP 8.x does accept that syntax but does NOT run
   the AAR through its packaging transforms — the compile-classpath
   gets `classes.jar` but `jniLibs/*.so` and AndroidManifest bits are
   silently dropped, so `Class.forName("paykeyfearnative.Paykeyfearnative")`
   succeeds at compile but `System.loadLibrary("gojni")` fails on device.
   Replace with a proper flatDir maven repo + `implementation(name=..., ext="aar")`,
   which DOES run the transforms. Verified in CI by unzipping the
   produced APK and grepping for `lib/arm64-v8a/libgojni.so` +
   `paykeyfearnative/Paykeyfearnative` in DEX.

2. QR scanner forced landscape. ZXing's library CaptureActivity is
   declared with `screenOrientation="sensorLandscape"`; runtime flags
   can't override a manifest attribute. Added
   `PortraitCaptureActivity : CaptureActivity()` and declared it in the
   app manifest with `screenOrientation="portrait"` + `tools:replace`,
   then pointed ScanOptions at the subclass.

3. AWG (and others') QR codes wouldn't scan. Two issues:
   a. Bare base64 Amnezia bundles (without `vpn://` prefix — what some
      desktop exporters emit) were rejected by AmneziaBundleParser.
      Now falls back to base64 decode + "{contains containers}" sniff.
   b. After scanning, the result only populated the text field —
      users had to press Import separately. Scan now auto-imports.

4. "No internet when connected". Fixing #1 restores all three native
   backends; tun was otherwise up but noop'd all packets.

CI gains:
- Umbrella .aar sanity check: must contain classes.jar +
  jni/arm64-v8a/libgojni.so before proceeding.
- Post-build APK inspection: verifies libgojni.so and bundle class
  survived R8 / packaging. Previous green builds produced stripped
  APKs with no warning.

Tests: extended AmneziaBundleParser suite with bare-base64 case.
